---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>Evidence-first supplement content, coming soon.</h1>
			<p>
				Supplement Hero is now set up as an Astro blog and ready for real research-backed content.
				Everything currently published is placeholder copy used to prove the repo, routes, and content
				pipeline are working.
			</p>
			<p>
				The current structure supports a homepage, an about page, a blog index, RSS, sitemap generation,
				and Markdown or MDX posts inside <code>src/content/blog/</code>.
			</p>
			<p>Recommended next steps:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Replace the placeholder posts with real supplement research and editorial copy</li>
				<li>Update the site URL in <code>astro.config.mjs</code> before deployment</li>
				<li>Swap placeholder images and branding for production assets</li>
				<li>Expand the about page with the real editorial standard and methodology</li>
			</ul>
			<p>
				Use the <a href="/blog">blog index</a> to review the current placeholder entries.
			</p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
